<ItacAcademyItem AcademyId="0114" RecordId="021-000005234"><Name>Accesi (Accademia degli)</Name><AlternativeName>Academia Accensorum</AlternativeName><City CityId="86"><CityItalianName>Palermo</CityItalianName><CityEnglishName>Palermo</CityEnglishName><CityLatinName>Panormus</CityLatinName></City><StartDate>1568</StartDate><EndDate>1581</EndDate><DateText>1568-1581</DateText><Notes>Maylender dates the foundation of the Accesi Academy to 1508 (Vol. I, p. 28). According to Gian Maria Mazzucchelli, Antonino Mongitore and Alessio Narbone, the said Academy was founded in 1568. See G Mazzucchelli, Gli Scrittori D`Italia, Brescia, 1753, pp. 36-37; Antonino Mongitore, Bibliotheca Sicula, Didaci Bua, Palermo, 1707, Vol.I, pp. 1-2 (British Library Shelfmark:610.m.10.); Alessio Narbone, Bibliografia Sicola Sistematica, Palermo, 1853, Vol. II, pp. 101-102 (British Library Shelfmark: 011903.f.3.).
